cs.CV, cs.MM, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about crowd counting in videos, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel network architecture, which involves modeling the temporal relationship between video frames, indicating that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia), which deals with the processing and analysis of multimedia data. The paper also mentions the use of deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper proposes a lightweight network to balance computational cost and representation ability, which could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
